<h1>
Coeliac disease
</h1>
<p>
Coeliac disease is an autoimmune disorder of the small intestine that occurs in genetically predisposed people of all ages from middle infancy onward. 
</p>
<p>
Symptoms include chronic diarrhoea, failure to thrive (in children) and fatigue, but these may be absent, and symptoms in other organ systems have been described.
</p>
